OL,4,Ca college and sports facilities
OL,6,FThe public is not expected to pay for
OL,7,Fthe projects with extra taxes.
OL,8,FInstead, from next year, the
OL,9,FGovernment's annual capital allocation
OL,10,F- approximately #80 million - will be
OL,11,Fringfenced in the new Jersey Capital
OL,12,FInvestment Fund.
OL,14,FWhere needed, money may also be
OL,15,Freallocated from other areas or
OL,16,Fborrowed to support major
OL,17,Finfrastructure projects.
OL,19,FMr Wylie also believes a change of
OL,20,Fapproach is needed for the island's
OL,21,Fhousing.
